beer.beer_description: This ‘new-world’ pale ale is late hopped with Amarillo for a subtle citrus aroma, dry hopped with Nelson Sauvin for a tropical finish and balanced with a pale malt and two specialty malts to deliver a sturdy caramel backbone. It leads the way for Cricketers Arms as the spearhead of our range. Great with classic gastro pub food – gourmet burger to porterhouse steak, to crumbed veal & fillets of chicken.
